<tr>
<td width="10"><img src="http://www.maximumeq.com/forum/Images/Message.gif" border="0"></td><td width="100%"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000"> <b>Wizard Attack Shields</b> <img src="http://www.maximumeq.com/forum/Images/New.gif" border="0"></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="EEEEEE">
<td><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000">Making Wizards more group friendly</font></td></tr></table></td></tr></table><p><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="CENTER" bgcolor="000000">
<tr>
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" align="CENTER">
<tr bgcolor="999999">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td width="10"><img src="http://www.maximumeq.com/forum/Images/SmallNew.gif" border="0" alt="New Message"></td><td width="50%"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="EEEEEE"><b>Wizard Attack Shields (modified 0 times)</b> </font></td><td width="50%" align="RIGHT"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="EEEEEE"><b>LoreWeaver</b></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="EEEEEE">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">What do the rest of you think about US as wizards getting a twist on Damage shields?  Instead we would have an Attack shield, one that deals damage everytime OUR tank connects with the mob.<br>
  <br>
  Example:  We cast O'Keils radiation on our Tank.  Now everytime he hits (lets say A Orc) O'keils deals 2 dmg to A Orc as well as whatever the Tank hits for, on a miss O'Keils doesn't deal any damage.  <br>
  <br>
  Nothing on O'Keils would need to be changed expect when it deals damage.. it's simple and makes us more group viable.  This would not only keep us masters of Direct damage, but would also allow us to continue dealing out More damage in less time by "Shielding" the melee types.  It could start with O'Keils and then go up with lvl, it would also give Wizards a way to affect those mobs out of our range finally without having us infringe on Druids or Mages Damage shields.  And seems like it would be easy to program into the existing code.<p>

  I was wondering what the rest of you think before I post this somewhere else.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000"><font size="1" color="000000">Mar 21, 2000</font><font size="1" color="000000"> 01:52:36 P.M.</font></font></td><td align="RIGHT"></td></tr></table></td></tr></table>
</td>
