<tr>
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" align="CENTER">
<tr bgcolor="999999">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td width="10"><img src="http://www.maximumeq.com/forum/Images/SmallNew.gif" border="0" alt="New Message"></td><td width="50%"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="EEEEEE"><b>RE:Wizard Attack Shields (modified 0 times)</b> </font></td><td width="50%" align="RIGHT"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="EEEEEE"><b>Zoso</b></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="EEEEEE">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">That is a good idea in theory, but I don't feel it is really needed.  Basicly what you are looking at is another combat buff.  With the DEX and STR buffs shaman have, they are able to have the tank miss less, and hit for more damage.  However, if you feel that Wizards need to compete with this, you might consider a spell that has a random chance of doing damage with every hit, similar to the necromancer spell that they are able to cast on themselves.  I for one just don't think that wizards need to concentrate on a "support" role.  Let the enchanters and shaman do all the work before a fight, and we can concern ourselves with ending the fight.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000"><font size="1" color="000000">Mar 22, 2000</font><font size="1" color="000000"> 05:22:04 A.M.</font></font></td><td align="RIGHT"></td></tr></table></td></tr></table>
